as opposed to `/[^\d]/g`?

without the global flag you can't guarantee that all non-numbers will be removed, only the first character. is that intentional?

```js
'fx123abc'.replace(/[^\d]/, '')
// 'x123abc'

'fx123abc'.replace(/[^\d]+/, '')
// '123abc'

'fx123abc'.replace(/[^\d]/g, '')
// '123'
